===Etymology===
Noun sense 1 (“(''obsolete'') plant known as mercury”) is from {{inh|en|enm|mercurial}}, {{m|enm|mercuryal||a plant, probably the goosefoot (''Chenopodium''); (''possibly'') dog's mercury (''Mercurialis perennis'')}},<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=mercuriāl|pos=n|id=MED27416|accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref> from {{der|en|xno|mercurial}} and {{der|en|fro|mercurial}}, or directly from their {{glossary|etymon}} {{der|en|la|mercuriālis||a plant, probably annual mercury (''Mercurialis annua'')}}, from {{m|la|mercuriālis||pertaining to the Roman god Mercury|pos=adjective}}, from {{m|la|Mercurius||the Roman god Mercury}} + {{m|la|-ālis|pos=''suffix forming adjectives of relationship from nouns''}}.<ref name="OED">{{R:OED Online|pos=n.'' and ''adj|id=116691|date=September 2001|nodot=yes}}; {{R:Oxford Dictionaries Online}}</ref>

Later adjective and noun uses may have been directly derived from {{der|en|la|mercuriālis|pos=adjective}},<ref name="OED"/> whence {{cog|enm|mercurial}}, {{m|enm|Mercurial||under the astrological influence of the planet Mercury}}.<ref>{{R:MED Online|entry=Mercuriāl|pos=adj|id=MED27417|accessdate=5 May 2019}}</ref>

